I've made this recipe many times over the last few years. I usually mix some jam into the glaze for a little twist. This last time, I replaced the corn syrup with a homemade coffee syrup. I took 1 cup of sugar and slowly melted it in a skillet over medium heat. I took a small coffee with two extra shots and reduced it about 30%. I added that to the molten sugar, then added another cup of sugar. I substituted this for the corn syrup in the exact quantity. It was killer!

