After reading nearly all 274 reviews this past weekend, I finally got up the courage to try this recipe. I think my first attempt at this was a great one. I would although do a few things differently next time. First of all, I decided to use 1/3 bittersweet and 2/3 semi-sweet chocolate. I personally think this was a wise decision. I cut back the sugar by a few tablespoons so it wouldn't be too sweet. I baked it at 340 degrees for 45 min. It did crack a bit but I expected that. Once I flipped it over you couldn't see the cracks anymore and it looked great. Instead of pushing down the sides like the recipe says I just pealed off the crust and didn't worry about it. Next, I tried to make the glaze (minus the corn syrup) and it turned into mush. I'm not sure why?? So, after dumping out the first glaze I tried it again but this time only used 1/2 semi sweet & 1/2 bittersweet chocolate (over 60% cocoa) It was perfect! Next time I'm going to use a shiny glaze recipe so it looks better. I garnished the cake with a few fresh raspberries in the middle. It looked beautiful...and tasted great. I set out fresh raspberries, cool whip and ice cream for the guests. Everyone loved it. I think using some semi-sweet chocolate was the trick. Good luck!

