simple, rich, and lovely! Two hints: use bittersweet chocolate- I used 88% cacao. Semisweet will make the cake a sugar bomb. And DO NOT OVERBEAT the egg whites, or you'll end up with a dry cake. Admittedly, I did modify a bit: my oven is unpredicatable, so I checked the cake at 40 min and took it out then. I didn't make the glaze, but I did tweak the recipe a bit: I shredded a ginger root and added it to the batter, and then served the cake with ginger whipped cream. (Put candied ginger and a generous amount of granulated sugar in the food processor, then beat this into heavy cream for ginger whipped cream.)

