Rating: 3
Very tasty. 0. Why chop the chocolate? You can melt big blocks of chocolate easily in a double-boiler setup. Get two pots that fit over each other; boil water in one, then place the second pot on top and throw in the chocolate, stirring frequently. Then add in the butter. 1. Beware of seizing chocolate. Chocolate and water do not mix. 2. Don't underbake. Cracks are OK, really. It's crispy on the bottom and light on the top. 3. The corn syrup in the glaze gives it a slightly different taste from the cake. You want that contrast, or else the glaze will suck!

