Rating: 1
I cannot understand why everyone is so crazy about this cake. My entire family are dyed-in-the-wool chocoholics and NO ONE liked this cake. It is way to bitter. I remade it using all semi-sweet chocolate and it was SO much better. And instead of all this changung plates and freezing the glaze, I added 1 cup of powdered sugar to the glaze after the chocolate had melted, beat it well for about 2 minutes and poured it on the top of the cake and pushed it over to the sides to drip down the sides of the cake. After the cake has cooled completely, just turn it over in your left hand and remove the bottom of the cake pan and the wax or parchment paper and put it on a large plate. Slip strips of wax paper under the cake, all around, leaving about 2" of the paper sticking out from under the cake. After the frosting...or glaze firms up, simply remove the strips of paper. The instructions for icing this cake are way more complicated than it should be.

